## The Naming Rosetta Stone

This is the most important section. It maps the home's actual device names — which may be
whimsical, historical, or deeply personal — to what they physically are and where they live.
An LLM that doesn't have this will make confident wrong guesses.

### Speakers and media players

| Name / entity | What it actually is | Location |
|---|---|---|
| `media_player.living_room` | HEOS speaker, labelled "Music Room" | Main living/music area |
| `media_player.kitchen` | HEOS speaker "Kitchen" | Kitchen |
| `media_player.lefty` | HEOS speaker "Lefty" (one half of a pair) | [ROOM] |
| `media_player.pancho` | HEOS speaker "Pancho" (one half of a pair) | [ROOM] |
| Lefty + Pancho | HEOS group — use as Spotify target | [ROOM] — grouped stereo pair |
| `media_player.rozi_office` | HEOS speaker in Rozi's office | Rozi Office |

> Note: HEOS-labelled room names in Spotify's `source_list` do not always match HA entity IDs.
> e.g. "Music Room" in source_list → `media_player.living_room` in HA. The wrappers handle this.

### Lights — the amusing ones

Document lights with non-obvious names so the LLM doesn't confuse them with people, places, or things.

| Name / entity | What it physically is | Location / notes |
|---|---|---|
| `light.example_a` | Floor lamp by the window | Living room |
| `light.example_b` | Under-cabinet strip light | Kitchen |
| GROUP_NAME lights | Group of the above | [AREA] |

### Switches and plugs

| Name / entity | What it physically is | Location / notes |
|---|---|---|
| `switch.example` | Smart plug controlling the coffee maker | Kitchen counter |

### Other named devices

| Name / entity | What it physically is | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `YOUR_ENTITY` | Physical description | Any helpful context |

